		<p><span style="line-height:1.5em"><span style="font-size:20px">&nbsp; Congress and presidential elections will be scheduled 5 days prior to election day so that the candidates will have time for their election campaign.&nbsp;Elections will last 24 hours. They will start at 4 AM of the country timezone and end at 4 AM. </span></span></p>

		<p><span style="line-height:1.5em"><span style="font-size:20px">&nbsp; If there is only one candidate for presidential elections, then he will win even without a single vote. If there are 2 and more candidates and none of them got more than 50% of votes, then there will be new elections on the next day with only top 2 candidates participating in them. If there are only 2 candidates and both of them received the same number of votes, then new elections will be on the next day with the same candidates. So, in order to win presidential elections, one of the candidates must get more than 50% of votes.</span></span></p>

		<p><span style="line-height:1.5em"><span style="font-size:20px">&nbsp; In order to win congress elections, candidate or a party will need to get enough votes for at least one seat. Candidates can participate in elections as a single person or from the party. If a candidate is participating in elections from the party, then whether he will get into Congress or not&nbsp;depends on how many seats a party won and under what number the candidate is. If he&#39;s on the list under number 7 and the party won only 5 seats, then this candidate will not get into the Congress. Party founders can change the candidate number in the list and add or remove a party member from Congress candidates list.</span></span></p>

